{"timestamp":"2026-02-12T22:46:52.725Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"call_0E8foOJyK8wX2eUBcHCma3Tn","output":"Chunk ID: a66b91\nWall time: 0.0519 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1072\nOutput:\n3://! Orchestrates the decision of whether to push notes to the remote after\n9://!    attached locally only (no push).\n10://! 3. **Autopush consent**: `git config ai.session-commit-linker.autopush` -- on first\n11://!    push for a repo, print a warning and record consent. After that,\n12://!    push silently.\n16://! ALL processing (not just push).\n27:/// Determine whether notes should be pushed for this repository.\n30:/// org filter, and autopush consent.\n32:/// Returns `true` if all conditions are met and notes should be pushed.\n33:/// Returns `false` if any condition prevents pushing.\n34:pub fn should_push() -> bool {\n46:    // Check 3: Autopush consent\n54:/// Attempt to push notes to the remote. Handles failure gracefully.\n58:pub fn attempt_push() {\n59:    if let Err(e) = git::push_notes() {\n61:            \"[ai-session-commit-linker] warning: failed to push notes: {}\",\n74:/// Returns `true` if push is allowed (no filter, or filter matches).\n79:        // No org filter configured: allow push\n86:        // If we can't read remotes, don't push\n105:/// Check autopush consent. On first push for a repo, print a warning to\n106:/// stderr and record consent by setting `git config ai.session-commit-linker.autopush true`.\n111:    match git::config_get(\"ai.session-commit-linker.autopush\") {\n113:            // Consent already recorded, push silently\n117:            // Explicitly opted out of push\n121:            // Not set or error reading: this is the first push for this repo.\n126:    // First push for this repo: print informational warning\n128:        \"[ai-session-commit-linker] This is the first time AI Session Commit Linker will push notes for this repository.\"\n130:    eprintln!